javadoc:
Column Constraint where acceptable column values are not within some range defined by a min value and
 a max value.

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment:
Construct a new NotInDateRangeConstraint that uses the default name and group and specifies the min
 and max values for the range.

params.name: minValue
params.comment: the min value of the excluded range.

params.name: maxValue
params.comment: the max value of the excluded range.

params.name: editorProvider
params.comment: an object that can provide an appropriate range editor for the column type.

name: NotInDateRangeColumnConstraint
comment:
Column Constraint where acceptable column values are not within some range defined by a min value and
 a max value.
